Characters . Adult SVL 65.0– 83.8 mm , supranasal single; dorsal tubercle rows 15–25 ; webbing between fingers and toes absent; tubercles on limbs present; number of precoacal and femoral pores in males 8–11 ; postcloacal tubercles 2–4 ; tail dorsally with tubercles; without enlarged subcaudals; dorsal body blotched.

subSubSection.paragraph: Distribution. The species of this group are more widespread distributed in northern and central Laos including Khammouane, Champasak, and Salavan provinces. These species have a tree-dwelling life style.
